The <b>Large-billed Tern</b> (<i>Phaetusa simplex</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tern" title="Tern">tern</a> in the Sternidae family. It belongs to the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monotypic" title="Monotypic" class="mw-redirect">monotypic</a> genus <i><b>Phaetusa</b></i>.
It is found in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argentina" title="Argentina">Argentina</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bolivia" title="Bolivia">Bolivia</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazil" title="Brazil">Brazil</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colombia" title="Colombia">Colombia</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecuador" title="Ecuador">Ecuador</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_Guiana" title="French Guiana">French Guiana</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guyana" title="Guyana">Guyana</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paraguay" title="Paraguay">Paraguay</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peru" title="Peru">Peru</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suriname" title="Suriname">Suriname</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trinidad_and_Tobago" title="Trinidad and Tobago">Trinidad and Tobago</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uruguay" title="Uruguay">Uruguay</a>, and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Venezuela" title="Venezuela">Venezuela</a>. It has occurred as a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vagrancy_in_birds" title="Vagrancy in birds" class="mw-redirect">vagrant</a> in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aruba" title="Aruba">Aruba</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bermuda" title="Bermuda">Bermuda</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cuba" title="Cuba">Cuba</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Panama" title="Panama">Panama</a> and the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a>.
Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitats</a> are <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/River" title="River">rivers</a> and freshwater <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lake" title="Lake">lakes</a>.
